        Condition.</div>
      <div style="text-indent: 21.6pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-transform: none;">On January 7, 2020, AngioDynamics, Inc. (&#8220;AngioDynamics&#8221;) issued a press
        release announcing financial results for the fiscal second quarter ended November&#160;30,&#160;2019. A copy of the press release is furnished herewith as Exhibit 99.1.</div>
      <div style="text-indent: 21.6pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-transform: none;">The information set forth in Item 2.02 of this Form 8-K (including
        Exhibit 99.1) shall not be deemed &#8220;filed&#8221; for purposes of Section 18 of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended (the &#8220;Exchange Act&#8221;), or otherwise subject to the liabilities under that Section. Furthermore, such information shall not be
        deemed to be incorporated by reference into any filing under the Securities Act of 1933, as amended (the &#8220;Securities Act&#8221;) or the Exchange Act, except as shall be expressly set forth by specific reference in such a filing.</div>
      <div style="text-align: left; margin-bottom: 6pt; font-weight: bold; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-transform: none;">Item 7.01 &#8211;&#160;Regulation FD Disclosure.</div>
      <div style="text-indent: 21.75pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-transform: none;">Presentation slides discussing AngioDynamics and its fiscal second
        quarter ended November 30, 2019 are furnished herewith as Exhibit 99.2.</div>
      <div style="text-indent: 21.75pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-transform: none;">The presentation slides furnished pursuant to Item 7.01 of this Form 8-K
        (including Exhibit 99.2) shall not be deemed &#8220;filed&#8221; for purposes of Section 18 of the Exchange Act, or otherwise subject to the liabilities under that Section. Furthermore, the presentation slides shall not be deemed to be incorporated by
        reference into any filing under the Securities Act or the Exchange Act, except as shall be expressly set forth by specific reference in such a filing.</div>
      <div style="text-align: left; margin-bottom: 6pt; font-weight: bold; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-transform: none;">Forward-Looking Statements</div>
      <div style="text-indent: 18pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-transform: none;">This document and its attachments contain forward-looking statements within
        the meaning of the Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995. All statements regarding AngioDynamics&#8217; expected future financial position, results of operations, cash flows, business strategy, budgets, projected costs, capital expenditures,
        products, competitive positions, growth opportunities, plans and objectives of management for future operations, as well as statements that include the words such as &#8220;expects,&#8221; &#8220;reaffirms,&#8221; &#8220;intends,&#8221; &#8220;anticipates,&#8221; &#8220;plans,&#8221; &#8220;believes,&#8221; &#8220;seeks,&#8221;
        &#8220;estimates,&#8221; &#8220;optimistic,&#8221; or variations of such words and similar expressions, are forward-looking statements. These forward-looking statements are not guarantees of future performance and are subject to risks and uncertainties. Investors are
        cautioned that actual events or results may differ from AngioDynamics&#8217; expectations. Factors that may affect the actual results achieved by AngioDynamics include, without limitation, the ability of AngioDynamics to develop its existing and new
        products, technological advances and patents attained by competitors, infringement of AngioDynamics&#8217; technology or assertions that AngioDynamics&#8217; technology infringes the technology of third parties, the ability of AngioDynamics to effectively
        compete against competitors that have substantially greater resources, future actions by the FDA or other regulatory agencies, domestic and foreign health care reforms and government regulations, results of pending or future clinical trials,
        overall economic conditions, the results of on-going litigation, challenges with respect to third-party distributors or joint venture partners or collaborators, the results of sales efforts, the effects of product recalls and product liability
        claims, changes in key personnel, the ability of AngioDynamics to execute on strategic initiatives, the effects of economic, credit and capital market conditions, general market conditions, market acceptance, foreign currency exchange rate
        fluctuations, the effects on pricing from group purchasing organizations and competition, the ability of AngioDynamics to integrate purchased businesses, as well as the risk factors listed from time to time in AngioDynamics&#8217; SEC filings, including
        but not limited to its Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended May 31, 2019. AngioDynamics does not assume any obligation to publicly update or revise any forward-looking statements for any reason.</div>

              <div align="left" style="margin-left: 0pt; text-indent: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt;">By: </div>
            </td>

  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt;"><br style="line-height: 13.7pt;">
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">AngioDynamics, Inc.</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">Stephen Trowbridge, SVP General Counsel and Interim CFO</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; margin-bottom: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">(518) 795-1408</div>
  <div style="text-align: center; line-height: 20.5pt; margin-bottom: 16.5pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 18pt; font-weight: bold;">AngioDynamics Reports Fiscal 2020 Second Quarter Financial Results</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt; font-style: italic; font-weight: bold;"><a name="z_Hlk12958193"></a>Fiscal 2020 Second Quarter Highlights</div>
  <div>
    <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" id="z8b5c54bcdc7e40198f026e997b238971" class="DSPFListTable" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 10pt; width: 100%; text-align: left; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

  <div>
    <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" id="z25f0c2fc356d4970940ee4f8b6564886" class="DSPFListTable" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 10pt; width: 100%; text-align: left; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

  <div>
    <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" id="z3f04b439ad3648e19ce15f3420675c8a" class="DSPFListTable" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 10pt; width: 100%; text-align: left; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

        <tr>
          <td style="width: 22.5pt; vertical-align: top;">

          <td style="width: auto; vertical-align: top;">
            <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-size: 12pt; font-weight: bold;">GAAP loss per share of $0.07; adjusted earnings per share of $0.06</div>
          </td>

  <div>
    <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" id="zaf56e3b84dfb49b39e37e69dd8b7eeca" class="DSPFListTable" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 10pt; width: 100%; text-align: left; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

        <tr>
          <td style="width: 22.5pt; vertical-align: top;">
            <div style="margin-left: 4.5pt; line-height: 13.7pt; font-size: 12pt; font-weight: bold;">&#8226;</div>
          </td>
          <td style="width: auto; vertical-align: top;">
            <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-size: 12pt; font-weight: bold;">Announces the acquisition of C3 Wave PICC tip location system subsequent to quarter end</div>
          </td>
        </tr>

    </table>
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt;"><br style="line-height: 13.7pt;">
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;"><font style="font-weight: bold;">Latham, New York, January 7, 2020 </font><font style="font-weight: bold;">&#8211;</font>&#160;AngioDynamics, Inc.&#160;(NASDAQ: ANGO),&#160;a
    leading provider of innovative, minimally invasive medical devices for vascular access, peripheral vascular disease, and oncology, today announced financial results for the second quarter of&#160;fiscal&#160;year 2020, which ended November 30, 2019.</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt;"><br style="line-height: 13.7pt;">
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">&#8220;Sales growth of 2.5%, ex-Asclera, exhibited continued momentum during the quarter, and I am pleased with the resulting gross margin expansion and
    profitability,&#8221; commented Jim Clemmer, President and Chief Executive Officer of AngioDynamics, Inc. &#8220;We are making excellent progress on the integration of Eximo Medical and are currently building out a dedicated commercial organization to support a
    product launch in the second half of our fiscal year 2020. I&#8217;m also excited to announce the acquisition of the C3 Wave tip location product, which will fill a technology gap in our portfolio and enable broader market adoption of our innovative BioFlo
    PICCs. Looking ahead, strong growth in sales of our AngioVac and NanoKnife products during the quarter should position us well to achieve our full-year guidance and drive growth across our portfolio.&#8221;</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt;"><br style="line-height: 13.7pt;">
  </div>
  <div id="DSPFPageBreakArea" style="clear: both; margin-top: 10pt; margin-bottom: 10pt;">
    <div id="DSPFPageBreak" style="page-break-after: always;">
      <hr noshade="noshade" style="margin: 4px 0px; width: 100%; border-width: 0px; height: 2px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); clear: both;"></div>
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt;"><br style="line-height: 13.7pt;">
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt; font-weight: bold;">Second Quarter 2020 Financial Results</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">&#160;</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">Net sales for the second quarter of fiscal 2020, which now include the fiscal year 2019 acquisitions of BioSentry and RadiaDyne as organic revenue, were $70.0
    million, flat compared to the prior-year quarter. Excluding the impact of Asclera sales, which were discontinued during fiscal year 2019, net sales grew 2.5% year over year. Foreign currency translation did not have a significant impact on the
    Company&#8217;s sales in the quarter.</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">&#160;</div>
  <div style="text-indent: -22.5pt; margin-left: 22.5pt; line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">&#8226;<font style="font-size: 9pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font>Oncology net sales were $16.1 million, an increase of 5.1% from $15.3
    million a year ago, led by higher sales of NanoKnife and the Alatus and IsoLoc balloon products.</div>
  <div style="text-indent: -22.5pt; margin-left: 22.5pt; line-height: 6.85pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 9pt;">&#160;</div>
  <div style="text-indent: -22.5pt; margin-left: 22.5pt; line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">&#8226;<font style="font-size: 9pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font>Vascular Interventions and Therapies (&#8220;VIT&#8221;) net sales were $31.2
    million, an increase of 0.6%, compared to $31.0 million a year ago. Excluding last year&#8217;s Asclera sales of $1.7 million in the second quarter, VIT grew 6.5%, driven by growth in sales of the Company&#8217;s AngioVac and core VIT products.</div>
  <div style="text-indent: -22.5pt; margin-left: 22.5pt; line-height: 6.85pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 9pt;">&#160;</div>
  <div style="text-indent: -22.5pt; margin-left: 22.5pt; line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">&#8226;<font style="font-size: 9pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font>Vascular Access net sales were $22.8 million, a decrease of 4.0% from
    $23.7 million a year ago, due primarily to lower sales of Ports and PICCs.</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">&#160;</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">Excluding Asclera, U.S. net sales in the second quarter of fiscal 2020 were $55.6 million, an increase of 1.8% from $54.6 million a year ago, and International
    net sales were $14.4 million, an increase of 5.6% from $13.7 million a year ago.</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">&#160;</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">Gross margin for the second quarter of fiscal 2020 was 59.3%, an increase of 140 basis points compared to the second quarter of fiscal 2019, driven primarily
    by productivity and supply chain improvements as well as positive product mix.</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">&#160;</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">The Company recorded a net loss from continuing operations of $2.7 million, or a loss of $0.07 per share, in the second quarter of fiscal 2020. This compares
    to a net loss from continuing operations of approximately $3.6 million, or a loss of&#160;$0.10 per share, a year ago.</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">&#160;</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">Excluding the items shown in the non-GAAP reconciliation table below, adjusted net income for the second quarter of fiscal 2020 was $2.2 million, or $0.06 per
    share, compared to adjusted net income of $2.9 million, or $0.07 per share, in the second quarter of fiscal 2019.</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">&#160;</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">Adjusted EBITDA in the second quarter of fiscal 2020, excluding the items shown in the reconciliation table below, was $6.4 million, compared to $9.0 million
    in the second quarter of fiscal 2019.</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">&#160;</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">In the second quarter of fiscal 2020, the Company used $5.9 million in operating cash and had capital expenditures of $2.6 million. As of November 30, 2019,
    the Company had $41.2 million in cash and cash equivalents and no debt outstanding.</div>
  <div id="DSPFPageBreakArea" style="clear: both; margin-top: 10pt; margin-bottom: 10pt;">
    <div id="DSPFPageBreak" style="page-break-after: always;">
      <hr noshade="noshade" style="margin: 4px 0px; width: 100%; border-width: 0px; height: 2px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); clear: both;"></div>
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt;"><br style="line-height: 13.7pt;">
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt; font-weight: bold;">Six Months Financial Results</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt;"><br style="line-height: 13.7pt;">
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">For the six months ended November 30, 2019:</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt;"><br style="line-height: 13.7pt;">
  </div>
  <div>
    <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" id="z377c9ededc454ee28ddb56750dc3a0fd" class="DSPFListTable" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 10pt; width: 100%; text-align: left; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

        <tr>
          <td style="width: 18pt; vertical-align: top;">
            <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-size: 12pt;">&#8226;</div>
          </td>
          <td style="width: auto; vertical-align: top;">
            <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-size: 12pt;">Net sales were $136.0 million, an increase of 1.6%, compared to $133.9 million for the same period a year ago. Excluding the impact of Asclera, sales of which were discontinued during fiscal
              year 2019, net sales grew 4.0% year over year.</div>
          </td>
        </tr>

    </table>
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt;"><br style="line-height: 13.7pt;">
  </div>
  <div>
    <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" id="zb56c9975968c4a32b0406fcecfa3eaec" class="DSPFListTable" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 10pt; width: 100%; text-align: left; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

        <tr>
          <td style="width: 18pt; vertical-align: top;">
            <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-size: 12pt;">&#8226;</div>
          </td>
          <td style="width: auto; vertical-align: top;">
            <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-size: 12pt;">The Company's net loss from continuing operations was $4.0 million, or a loss of $0.11 per share, compared to a net loss from continuing operations of $9.3 million, or a loss of $0.25 per
              share, a year ago.</div>
          </td>
        </tr>

    </table>
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt;"><br style="line-height: 13.7pt;">
  </div>
  <div>
    <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" id="zf30513dcbf6f451da17150db1dc530f9" class="DSPFListTable" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 10pt; width: 100%; text-align: left; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

        <tr>
          <td style="width: 18pt; vertical-align: top;">
            <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-size: 12pt;">&#8226;</div>
          </td>
          <td style="width: auto; vertical-align: top;">
            <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-size: 12pt;">Gross margin improved 150 basis points to 58.6% from 57.1% a year ago.</div>
          </td>
        </tr>

    </table>
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt;"><br style="line-height: 13.7pt;">
  </div>
  <div>
    <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" id="z353de373ebd54282b5f0c284b0e1023d" class="DSPFListTable" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 10pt; width: 100%; text-align: left; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

        <tr>
          <td style="width: 18pt; vertical-align: top;">
            <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-size: 12pt;">&#8226;</div>
          </td>
          <td style="width: auto; vertical-align: top;">
            <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-size: 12pt;">Excluding the items shown in the non-GAAP reconciliation table below, adjusted net income was $5.3 million, or $0.14 per share, compared to adjusted net income of $3.6 million, or $0.09 per
              share, a year ago.</div>
          </td>
        </tr>

    </table>
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt;"><br style="line-height: 13.7pt;">
  </div>
  <div>
    <table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" id="z30ed3e05a8d1426181f814b406a00a8d" class="DSPFListTable" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 10pt; width: 100%; text-align: left; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">

        <tr>
          <td style="width: 18pt; vertical-align: top;">
            <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-size: 12pt;">&#8226;</div>
          </td>
          <td style="width: auto; vertical-align: top;">
            <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-size: 12pt;">Adjusted EBITDA, excluding the items shown in the reconciliation table below, was $13.7 million, compared to $14.4 million for the same period a year ago.</div>
          </td>
        </tr>

    </table>
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt;"><br style="line-height: 13.7pt;">
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt; font-weight: bold;">C3 Wave PICC Tip Location Acquisition</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt;"><br style="line-height: 13.7pt;">
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">Today, the Company announces the acquisition of the C3 Wave PICC tip location system from Medical Components Inc. This innovative, wireless, app-based ECG
    system eliminates the need for a confirmatory chest x-ray of PICC tip placement, allowing greater patient access to the Company&#8217;s proprietary BioFlo PICCs. The C3 Wave PICC tip location system has received FDA 510k, CE, Health Canada, and other
    international approvals.</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt;"><br style="line-height: 13.7pt;">
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt; font-weight: bold;">Fiscal&#160;Year 2020 Financial Guidance</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">&#160;</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">The Company reiterates its fiscal year 2020 guidance, which includes investments related to the full-market launch of the products acquired from Eximo
    anticipated in the second half of the fiscal year.</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt;"><br style="line-height: 13.7pt;">
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">Specifically, the Company continues to expect net sales in the range of $280 to $286 million and gross margin in the range of 58% to 59%. Adjusted earnings per
    share is expected in the range of $0.10 to $0.15.</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt; font-weight: bold;">&#160;</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt; font-weight: bold;">Conference Call</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">&#160;</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">The Company&#8217;s management will host a conference call today at 8:00 a.m. ET to discuss its fiscal 2020 second quarter results.</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">&#160;</div>
  <div id="DSPFPageBreakArea" style="clear: both; margin-top: 10pt; margin-bottom: 10pt;">
    <div id="DSPFPageBreak" style="page-break-after: always;">
      <hr noshade="noshade" style="margin: 4px 0px; width: 100%; border-width: 0px; height: 2px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); clear: both;"></div>
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt;"><br style="line-height: 13.7pt;">
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">To participate in the conference call, dial 1-877-407-0784 (domestic) or +1-201-689-8560 (international) and refer to the passcode 13697417.</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt;"><br style="line-height: 13.7pt;">
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">This conference call will also be webcast and can be accessed from the &#8220;Investors&#8221; section of the AngioDynamics website at <u><font style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: normal; color: rgb(0, 0, 225); font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-transform: none;">www.angiodynamics.com</font></u>. The webcast replay of the call will be available at the same site approximately one
    hour after the end of the call.</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt;"><br style="line-height: 13.7pt;">
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">A recording of the call will also be available from 11:00 a.m. ET on Tuesday, January 7, 2020, until 11:59 p.m. ET on Tuesday, January 14, 2020. To hear this
    recording, dial 1-844-512-2921 (domestic) or +1-412-317-6671 (international) and enter the passcode 13697417.</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt;"><br style="line-height: 13.7pt;">
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt; font-weight: bold;">Use of Non-GAAP Measures</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">&#160;</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">Management uses non-GAAP measures to establish operational goals and believes that non-GAAP measures may assist investors in analyzing the underlying trends in
    AngioDynamics' business over time. Investors should consider these non-GAAP measures in addition to, not as a substitute for or as superior to, financial reporting measures prepared in accordance with GAAP. In this news release, AngioDynamics has
    reported adjusted EBITDA, adjusted net income, adjusted earnings per share, free cash flow and net sales excluding Asclera. Management uses these measures in its internal analysis and review of operational performance. Management believes that these
    measures provide investors with useful information in comparing AngioDynamics' performance over different periods. By using these non-GAAP measures, management believes that investors get a better picture of the performance of AngioDynamics' underlying
    business. Management encourages investors to review AngioDynamics' financial results prepared in accordance with GAAP to understand AngioDynamics' performance taking into account all relevant factors, including those that may only occur from time to
    time but have a material impact on AngioDynamics' financial results. Please see the tables that follow for a reconciliation of non-GAAP measures to measures prepared in accordance with GAAP.</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt; font-weight: bold;">&#160;</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt; font-weight: bold;">About AngioDynamics, Inc.</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt; font-weight: bold;">&#160;</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">AngioDynamics, Inc.&#160;is a leading provider of innovative, minimally invasive medical devices used by professional healthcare providers for vascular access,
    peripheral vascular disease,&#160;and oncology. AngioDynamics&#8217;&#160;diverse product lines include market-leading ablation systems, vascular access products, angiographic products and accessories, drainage products, thrombolytic products and venous products. For
    more information, visit&#160;<u><font style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: normal; color: rgb(0, 0, 225); font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-transform: none;">www.angiodynamics.com</font></u>.</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt;"><br style="line-height: 13.7pt;">
  </div>
  <div id="DSPFPageBreakArea" style="clear: both; margin-top: 10pt; margin-bottom: 10pt;">
    <div id="DSPFPageBreak" style="page-break-after: always;">
      <hr noshade="noshade" style="margin: 4px 0px; width: 100%; border-width: 0px; height: 2px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); clear: both;"></div>
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt;"><br style="line-height: 13.7pt;">
  </div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt; font-weight: bold;">Safe Harbor</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt; font-weight: bold;">&#160;</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">This release contains forward-looking statements within the meaning of the Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995. All statements regarding
    AngioDynamics' expected future financial position, results of operations, cash flows, business strategy, budgets, projected costs, capital expenditures, products, competitive positions, growth opportunities, plans and objectives of management for
    future operations, as well as statements that include the words such as "expects," "reaffirms," "intends," "anticipates," "plans," "believes," "seeks," "estimates," "optimistic," or variations of such words and similar expressions, are forward-looking
    statements. These forward-looking statements are not guarantees of future performance and are subject to risks and uncertainties. Investors are cautioned that actual events or results may differ from AngioDynamics' expectations. Factors that may affect
    the actual results achieved by AngioDynamics include, without limitation, the ability of AngioDynamics to develop its existing and new products, technological advances and patents attained by competitors, infringement of AngioDynamics' technology or
    assertions that AngioDynamics' technology infringes the technology of fourth parties, the ability of AngioDynamics to effectively compete against competitors that have substantially greater resources, future actions by the FDA or other regulatory
    agencies, domestic and foreign health care reforms and government regulations, results of pending or future clinical trials, overall economic conditions, the results of on-going litigation, challenges with respect to fourth-party distributors or joint
    venture partners or collaborators, the results of sales efforts, the effects of product recalls and product liability claims, changes in key personnel, the ability of AngioDynamics to execute on strategic initiatives, the effects of economic, credit
    and capital market conditions, general market conditions, market acceptance, foreign currency exchange rate fluctuations, the effects on pricing from group purchasing organizations and competition, the ability of AngioDynamics to integrate acquired
    businesses, as well as the risk factors listed from time to time in AngioDynamics' SEC filings, including but not limited to its Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended May 31, 2019. AngioDynamics does not assume any obligation to publicly update
    or revise any forward-looking statements for any reason.</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">&#160;</div>
  <div style="line-height: 13.7pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',Times,serif; font-size: 12pt;">In the United States, the NanoKnife System has received a 510(k) clearance by the Food and Drug Administration for use in the surgical ablation of soft
    tissue&#160;and is similarly approved for commercialization in Canada, the European Union,&#160;and Australia. The NanoKnife System has not been cleared for the treatment or therapy of a specific disease or condition.</div>

            expenditures, products, competitive positions, growth opportunities, plans and objectives of management for future operations, as well as statements that include the words such as &#8220;expects,&#8221; &#8220;reaffirms,&#8221; &#8220;intends,&#8221; &#8220;anticipates,&#8221; &#8220;plans,&#8221;

            uncertainties. Investors are cautioned that actual events or results may differ from AngioDynamics&#8217; expectations. Factors that may affect the actual results achieved by AngioDynamics include, without limitation, the ability of AngioDynamics to
            develop its existing and new products, technological advances and patents attained by competitors, infringement of AngioDynamics&#8217; technology or assertions that AngioDynamics&#8217; technology infringes the technology of third parties, the ability of
            AngioDynamics to effectively compete against competitors that have substantially greater resources, future actions by the FDA or other regulatory agencies, domestic and foreign health care reforms and government regulations, results of pending
            or future clinical trials, overall economic conditions, the results of on-going litigation, challenges with respect to third-party distributors or joint venture partners or collaborators, the results of sales efforts, the effects of product
            recalls and product liability claims, changes in key personnel, the ability of AngioDynamics to execute on strategic initiatives, the effects of economic, credit and capital market conditions, general market conditions, market acceptance,
            foreign currency exchange rate fluctuations, the effects on pricing from group purchasing organizations and competition, the ability of AngioDynamics to integrate acquired businesses, as well as the risk factors listed from time to time in
            AngioDynamics&#8217; SEC filings, including but not limited to its Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended May 31, 2019. AngioDynamics does not assume any obligation to publicly update or revise any forward-looking statements for any reason.In
            the United States, the NanoKnife System has received a 510(k) clearance by the Food and Drug Administration for use in the surgical ablation of soft tissue, and is similarly approved for commercialization in Canada, the European Union and
            Australia. The NanoKnife System has not been cleared for the treatment or therapy of a specific disease or condition.Notice Regarding Non-GAAP Financial MeasuresManagement uses non-GAAP measures to establish operational goals and believes that
            non-GAAP measures may assist investors in analyzing the underlying trends in AngioDynamics&#8217; business over time. Investors should consider these non-GAAP measures in addition to, not as a substitute for or as superior to, financial reporting
            measures prepared in accordance with GAAP. In this presentation, AngioDynamics has reported adjusted EBITDAS (income before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization and stock-based compensation); adjusted net income; adjusted earnings per
            shar, free cash flow and net sales on an organic basis, excluding acquired assets and Asclera. Management uses these measures in its internal analysis and review of operational performance. Management believes that these measures provide
            investors with useful information in comparing AngioDynamics&#8217; performance over different periods. By using these non-GAAP measures, management believes that investors get a better picture of the performance of AngioDynamics&#8217; underlying
            business. Management encourages investors to review AngioDynamics&#8217; financial results prepared in accordance with GAAP to understand AngioDynamics&#8217; performance taking into account all relevant factors, including those that may only occur from
            time to time but have a material impact on AngioDynamics&#8217; financial results. Please see the tables that follow for a reconciliation of non-GAAP measures to measures prepared in accordance with GAAP.&#160;&#160;Forward-Looking Statements&#160;</font></div>
